A commissioner in the Zamfara Independent Electoral Commission, Alhaji Hashimu-Shehu Gazura, is dead. He died in a ghastly accident on Friday. The News Agency of Nigeria reports that Gazura was also a former member, Zamfara House of Assembly, who represented Gummi 2 Constituency. His death is contained in a statement issued in Gusau on Saturday by the Chairman, House of Assembly Service Commission, Mansur Bungudu. Bungudu said, “He died yesterday (Friday) as a result of a ghastly motor accident on Yawuri Road in Kebbi State. “The deceased’s funeral prayer is scheduled to be held at Gummi Emir’s Palace on Saturday (today) by 11:00 a.m.” NAN